Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.04,0:00:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I just stopped\Nby to thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.18,0:00:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for letting me borrow your\NDaring Do books! I love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.81,0:00:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait till you get to "Daring Do\Nand the Riddle of the Sphinx!"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.08,0:00:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually my\Nsecond time through!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.59,0:00:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read them all,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.92,0:00:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from "Daring Do and\Nthe Sapphire Statue"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.09,0:00:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to "Daring Do and the\NFallen Idol!"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Fallen Idol? That's\Nnot in the series.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.90,0:00:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it just came\Nout last week...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.43,0:00:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's why you\Nhaven't heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.10,0:00:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No way Daring Do's\Nbiggest fan, ME,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.34,0:00:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,would miss a\Nbook coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.91,0:00:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, A.K. Yearling\N{\i1}always{\i0} sends me a copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.68,0:00:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm happy to\Nlet you borrow mine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,until yours arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.45,0:00:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"The true story of\Nthe thieving fraud
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.08,0:00:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,known as Daring\NDo?" WHAT?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.49,0:00:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would A.K. Yearling\Nwrite that about herself!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.09,0:00:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It looks\Nlike she didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.49,0:01:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This book says it's by\NGroom Q. Q. Martingale.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.70,0:01:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.33,0:01:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess he's a\Nnew writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.87,0:01:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A BAD one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.47,0:01:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"The only thing worse\Nthan Daring Do's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.14,0:01:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,destruction of temples
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.74,0:01:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is her cruelty to the\Nmild-mannered Dr. Caballeron!?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.61,0:01:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}was{\i0} written from\Nhis point of view...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.08,0:01:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured it was\Nan artistic choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.11,0:01:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,More like a disaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.75,0:01:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen: "Daring Do isn't\Njust a fictional character
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.89,0:01:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from over-the-top\Nadventure stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I've met her, and she\Nis a real, live pony!"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.89,0:01:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's supposed\Nto be a secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.74,0:01:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the only ones\Nwho know Daring Do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.90,0:01:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is really A.K.\NYearling in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.30,0:01:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But if other ponies\Nread this book,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.20,0:01:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how long will it take\Nthem to figure that out?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.50,0:01:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go\Nwarn her!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.37,0:01:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,FLUTTERSHY!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.54,0:01:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Oh. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.98,0:02:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A.K. Yearling is\Nsigning all her books
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bookstore today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.85,0:02:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We can warn her about\Nwhat's going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.79,0:02:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think you should\Nread Martingale's book first?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.19,0:02:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to hear both\Nsides of the story?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.39,0:02:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, why? The only true\Nthing in that pack of LIES
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.10,0:02:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is that Daring Do is REAL.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.06,0:02:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also a\Nlot of insight
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.57,0:02:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,into Dr. Caballeron's\Nlife choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.30,0:02:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know he's actually\Na history professor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.64,0:02:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and amateur bird watcher?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.77,0:02:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious\Nright now!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.74,0:02:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A random writer TRASHES our\Nfriend and exposes her secret
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.01,0:03:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wanna\Ntalk ABOUT BIRDS!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.68,0:03:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[whispering] Also spider cruelty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,WHAT?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to\Nadmit Daring Do
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.89,0:03:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,wrecks a lot of spider\Nwebs in her adventures.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In order{\i0} to save precious\Nartifacts from the bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.69,0:03:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who you seem to have\Nforgotten is Dr. Caballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.83,0:03:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you read\Nthe same series I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.10,0:03:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at least A.K.\NYearling's TRUE fans
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.57,0:03:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,know Martingale's\Nbook is bogus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure those\Nare all fans...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.38,0:03:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't your books\Nsay Daring Do was real!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This changes everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.05,0:03:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And why do you only write\Nabout her good side?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.89,0:03:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she bribing you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.49,0:03:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,On page 531 it says\NDaring Do kicks puppies!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.86,0:03:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She does!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.18,0:03:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What!? No! Look,\Nare any of you here
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for my actual\Nbook signing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nuh-uh. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.57,0:03:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-uh. Frankly, I don't even know\Nhow you can call it {\i1}fiction{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.07,0:04:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's all real. You're as\Nmuch of a fake as Daring Do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.. I guess we're a little\Nlate to warn you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.08,0:04:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about the new book, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.48,0:04:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] I always feared\Nthat someday
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,everypony would learn\NDaring Do was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.76,0:04:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But why? Aren't you\Nproud of your adventures?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! But I'm not\Nin it for the fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.60,0:04:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The stories just seemed\Ntoo good to keep to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.27,0:04:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I knew who this\N"Martingale" author was,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and why he's determined to\Nruin my character... and me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.57,0:04:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we can ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.91,0:04:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! He's doing a\Nsigning across the street!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.65,0:04:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better\Ngo without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.18,0:04:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't risk the\Nchance Martingale
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.25,0:04:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,might recognize\Nme as Daring Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.48,0:04:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.99,0:04:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops! Um, sorry.\NExcuse us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.50,0:04:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] That's not Martingale!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.03,0:05:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Doctor Caballeron\Nin disguise!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.50,0:05:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it all makes sense!\NDaring Do's arch nemesis
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.47,0:05:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,created a fake "author"\Nself so he can write books
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.44,0:05:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that make him sound like\Na hero! Who does that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.18,0:05:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, A.K. Yearling?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.28,0:05:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is totally\Ndifferent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.28,0:05:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, well. Up to\Nyour old tricks again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.15,0:05:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like in Somnambula!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.75,0:05:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Spreading lies to make\NDaring Do look bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.56,0:05:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you sign our book?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.86,0:05:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I am just a simple author,\Ntelling it like it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.66,0:05:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Who should I make\Nit out to?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy, with two T's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.27,0:05:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh! We know who you\NREALLY are!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.37,0:05:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless you want us\Nto tell all of THEM,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.50,0:05:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd better answer\Nsome questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.74,0:05:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that's all\Nwe have time for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.08,0:05:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Awwww!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But please! Take a free copy\Nof my book on your way out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.05,0:05:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We aren't going to let you get\Naway with this, Caballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.56,0:06:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away with what? I am merely\Ntelling my side of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.73,0:06:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You think everything in A.K.\NYearling's books are true?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.93,0:06:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In "Daring Do and\Nthe Quetzal's Quest"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.80,0:06:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,she states that the\NFangthorn Flowers are red.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.94,0:06:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they are blue!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true. They are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Pfft! That sounds like more\Nof an editor's mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.25,0:06:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, if that is wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.12,0:06:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is it not possible that\Nother, bigger things are too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.22,0:06:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look! It's\Nin my book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.02,0:06:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't have to\Ntake YOUR word for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.96,0:06:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon, Fluttershy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.76,0:06:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.29,0:06:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It is terrible being\Nmisunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.10,0:06:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is true, in the past\NI have not been as nice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.13,0:06:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to Daring Do as I should.\NBut I have my reasons!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.77,0:06:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to talk about\Nwhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.21,0:06:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My team and I were\Nonly ever interested
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.31,0:06:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in researching\Nartifacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.38,0:06:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And taking them\Nto our museum
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.81,0:06:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} where other ponies{\i0}\N{\i1} could study them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.28,0:06:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.42,0:07:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But Daring Do always{\i0}\N{\i1} seemed to get there first,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.35,0:07:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} with her own plans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.49,0:07:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I offered to team up with{\i0}\N{\i1} her, but she refused.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.30,0:07:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} She had her own ideas of{\i0}\N{\i1} where the treasures belonged.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do {\i1}did{\i0} have\Na lot of artifacts
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.27,0:07:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,on her shelves at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But didn't {\i1}you{\i0} try to sell\Nthem to the highest bidder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.74,0:07:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Only because I\Nhad to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.41,0:07:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Since Daring Do kept{\i0}\N{\i1} taking our artifacts,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.44,0:07:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} our museum closed!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.55,0:07:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} We were desperate for{\i0}\N{\i1} money to keep it open.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.92,0:07:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She {\i1}does{\i0} destroy a\Nlot of ancient sites..
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the homes of\Nthe animals that live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.53,0:07:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I felt it was MY\Nduty to tell the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.60,0:07:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for listening\Nand understanding, Ms...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy. Two T's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.30,0:07:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am Dr.\NCaballeron.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Martingale is merely a nom\Nde plume to build my brand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:08:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, my team could\Nuse an insightful Pegasus
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,like you, Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.35,0:08:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever thought\Nof being.. an adventurer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.12,0:08:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Who, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.32,0:08:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.93,0:08:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally! What\Ntook you so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.46,0:08:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to find\Nout which author
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.33,0:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is {\i1}really{\i0} telling\Nthe truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.23,0:08:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so I joined Dr. C's\NTenochtitlan expedition!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.87,0:08:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [ominous music] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.20,0:08:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Say {\i1}WHAAAT?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.08,0:08:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So Daring Do doesn't\Nkick puppies?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.35,0:08:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That was ONE time.\NAccidentally!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.55,0:08:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A.K.! You have to help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.65,0:08:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Groom Q.Q. Martingale is\Nreally Dr. Caballeron,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.35,0:08:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has Fluttershy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The book thing was\Nhis new plan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.76,0:08:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to ruin Daring\NDo's reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.43,0:08:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,AND he's trying to make\Nmy friend a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.80,0:08:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They're off to\NTenochtitlan right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.43,0:08:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He must be after the Truth\NTalisman of Tonatiuh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.94,0:08:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It requires the wings of\Na Pegasus to retrieve it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.07,0:09:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's gotta be why\NCaballeron tricked Fluttershy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.41,0:09:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,into joining his gang!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.28,0:09:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's up to\Nus to stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.08,0:09:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.85,0:09:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.96,0:09:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch where you put\Nyour hooves, everypony.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.46,0:09:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not want to disturb the\Nfragile jungle ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.67,0:09:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's so thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.17,0:09:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, unlike Daring Do,\Nwho slashes plants aside
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.10,0:09:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with her cruel machete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.57,0:09:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.51,0:09:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fool! Don't you\Nknow that's poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.35,0:09:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to get\Nhurt, my friend. Heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.75,0:09:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.65,0:09:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can help\Nwith that! Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.92,0:09:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You are...willing\Nto share?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.96,0:09:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! That's\Npart of the fun
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.26,0:09:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of having an adventure\Nwith friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.38,0:10:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [tense music] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.35,0:10:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.51,0:10:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.58,0:10:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These ferocious beasts\Nwant to eat us for dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.49,0:10:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a common\Nmisconception.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever tried\Njust talking to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.66,0:10:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's crazy! You\Nare on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.43,0:10:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a goner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.73,0:10:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.43,0:10:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're very sorry for\Ncoming into your territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.47,0:10:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're just\Npassing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.10,0:10:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How...did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.44,0:10:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Everycreature likes\Nto be listened to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You just need to take the\Ntime to understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.71,0:10:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You are more talented\Nthan I realized..
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.15,0:10:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. I'm having the\Nbest time with you all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.52,0:10:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy must be\Nhaving the WORST time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.42,0:10:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with Caballeron's goons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.12,0:10:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to catch\Nup to them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:10:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,before they reach\Nthe truth talisman!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.79,0:11:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? What's so\Nspecial about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.96,0:11:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the power to\Nmake the pony holding it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.73,0:11:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.87,0:11:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But Caballeron only\Nwants it because
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.63,0:11:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it's made of\Nsolid gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.40,0:11:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll melt it down and\Nuse it to get rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.01,0:11:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So if this talisman\Nis so important,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.17,0:11:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,why didn't you\Nalready save it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.94,0:11:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You said only a Pegasus\Ncan get it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.18,0:11:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! But the temple traps\Nare far too dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.05,0:11:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to face without a map.\NAnd maybe even {\i1}with{\i0} one!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.35,0:11:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [military snare drum] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.52,0:11:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, how about we\Ntake the shortcut?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.03,0:11:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you\Nbe quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.43,0:11:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I mean... no\Nthank you, Biff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.56,0:11:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just\Nfollow the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.70,0:11:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw. I'm supposed to be Dr.\NC's second in command.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.14,0:11:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But he never\Nlistens to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.24,0:11:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, keep trying!\NI believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.18,0:11:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.58,0:11:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At last!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we simply have to\Nwait for the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.32,0:11:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach its\Nhighest point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.75,0:12:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And our path will\Nbe revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.19,0:12:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.76,0:12:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Withers. Don't. Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.37,0:12:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah ha ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.54,0:12:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.68,0:12:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We can catch them before\Nthey enter the temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.48,0:12:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Gah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.82,0:12:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back, Rainbow\NDash! It's Ahuizotl-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.42,0:12:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha? Gah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.46,0:12:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do. My old nemesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have outsmarted\Nmy jungle cats,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.90,0:12:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot escape ME!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! We didn't see any cats!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just here to\Nrescue Fluttershy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.84,0:12:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. It must be a coincidence\Nthat only a Pegasus
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.15,0:13:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,can retrieve\NTonatiuh's treasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are\Ntwo of you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.69,0:13:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.86,0:13:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.37,0:13:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [adventurous music] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.97,0:13:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly! Before the sun\Nmoves and it closes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.32,0:13:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.49,0:13:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew! {\i1}That{\i0} was\Ncutting it close.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.66,0:13:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And without a map, we'll have\Nto guess which way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.61,0:14:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! I knew\Nthe truth talisman
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.91,0:14:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,could not be moved by\Nmagic, but I never realized
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.88,0:14:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd have to FLY\Nto retrieve it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.02,0:14:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our journey has\Nbeen for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.72,0:14:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be upset,\NI can get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.06,0:14:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Fluttershy,\Nyou are too kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.42,0:14:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But I could never ask that of\Nyou. It might be dangerous..!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.53,0:14:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do it! For all\Nof you, my new friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.60,0:14:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And to protect a\Nhistorical treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.41,0:14:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.14,0:14:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a hoof here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.36,0:14:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [dark music] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.30,0:15:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.87,0:15:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.41,0:15:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, everypony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.54,0:15:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us the talisman,\NCaballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.98,0:15:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not taking\Nno for an answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.45,0:15:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! You don't understand.\NMy friends are researchers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.29,0:15:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They only want to\Nstudy the talisman
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.95,0:15:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep it safe in a\Nmuseum! Right, Dr. C?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.39,0:15:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... no.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! But... but...you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.13,0:15:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that he's holding\NTonatiuh's talisman,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.63,0:15:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he has to tell the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.50,0:15:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Admit it,\NCaballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.33,0:15:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only pretending\Nto like Fluttershy
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.24,0:15:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because she has the\Nwings you needed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.77,0:15:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to steal the\Ntruth talisman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.74,0:15:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.07,0:15:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.01,0:15:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I admit, that was\Nthe original reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.41,0:15:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But my henchponies and\NI have come to value
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.08,0:15:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,your friendship\Nand kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.78,0:15:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't see that\Ncoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.65,0:15:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Or that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.22,0:16:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,More intruders!? And you DARE\Nto steal Tonatiuh's talisman!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.29,0:16:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Guardian-goyles, ATTACK!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.89,0:16:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.01,0:16:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy! Can't you ask them\Nto stop, like the jungle cats!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, excuse me?\NUh, Guardian-goyles?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.89,0:16:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good! They're only\Nstone and magic, not alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.43,0:16:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I encountered some\Nlike this in Marapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.80,0:16:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. I seem to\Nrecall similar creations
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.40,0:16:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in Flankladesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.03,0:16:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So..? How do you\Nget rid of them!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.04,0:16:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know they don't\Nlike bright light!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.61,0:16:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's none of\Nthat in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet... Caballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.58,0:16:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still have the\NDiamond of Lapis-Lux?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.11,0:16:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I mean, YES.\NI mean... Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.52,0:17:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you know\N{\i1}I{\i0} stole it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.89,0:17:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky guess.\NHold it high!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [heroic music] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.90,0:17:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! You two make\Na great team!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm not sure\Nhow I feel about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel later! Now,\Nit's time to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.07,0:17:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If we want to get\Nout of here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.41,0:17:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all gonna have\Nto work TOGETHER.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.38,0:17:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...er actually\Na good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,See? Told you he'd listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.25,0:17:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A truce until we escape?\NBut how can we trust you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.75,0:17:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot lie. Now,\Nall together!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.83,0:17:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! You again!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.74,0:17:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If I wanted to\Nplay GAMES,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I would get out\Nmy pinochle deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.48,0:17:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.48,0:18:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.42,0:18:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainbow Dash!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.58,0:18:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.52,0:18:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna need the deluxe spa\Npackage after {\i1}this{\i0} adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.79,0:18:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't leave\Nthis temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! I'm quitting\Nthe henchpony business
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.47,0:18:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to finally follow my dreams\Nof becoming an opera star!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.68,0:18:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...maybe you\Nshould hold this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.01,0:18:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot hide in there\Nforever! It's a DEAD end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.65,0:18:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.59,0:18:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahuizotl won't give up\Nuntil he catches us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.59,0:18:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think our problem\Nis the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, did you forget there's\Na monster out there
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.73,0:18:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that wants to crush us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.20,0:18:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But WHY? Nopony\Never asked Ahuizotl
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.14,0:18:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what {\i1}his{\i0} side of\Nthe story is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.14,0:19:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He must have a reason\Nfor being so upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Or {\i1}maybe{\i0} he's\Njust a bad guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.14,0:19:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I need to remind you he\Ntried to squash Daring Do
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like a hundred times!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.78,0:19:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And me as well.\NI was so scared,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.58,0:19:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to change my ascot.\NAh! Curse this truth teller!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.92,0:19:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Understanding begins\Nwith listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.46,0:19:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepared to\Nmeet your DOOM!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.80,0:19:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, not really.\NJust here to ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.00,0:19:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you chasing\Nus, Mr. Ahuizotl?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.94,0:19:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the thing is,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.18,0:19:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in charge of\Nprotecting this jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.88,0:19:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If another artifact goes\Nmissing on my watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.05,0:19:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be\Nin SO much trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.65,0:19:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with the other\Nguardian creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.92,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! That sounds like a\Nlot of responsibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.66,0:19:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha--! It is! And those two have taken\Nso many relics from my land,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.73,0:19:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,my job is on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.77,0:20:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So maybe I am a little\Nviolent and ferocious..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.50,0:20:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you blame me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.44,0:20:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason I've\Nbeen taking the artifacts
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.45,0:20:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is because I {\i1}thought{\i0}\NI was protecting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.08,0:20:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was stealing\Nthem to get rich!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.45,0:20:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.. But I never realized\Nyou had a noble cause!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.35,0:20:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were\Njust being a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I get that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.33,0:20:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe there is\Nsomething to this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.13,0:20:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,whole "listening to\Neverypony" thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't always mean\Nthey're telling the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.13,0:20:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but everycreature\Ndeserves kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.20,0:20:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,True. And because you\Nreturned the talisman
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.61,0:20:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and took the time\Nto understand me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.21,0:20:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I will let you all go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.38,0:20:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,On one condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.92,0:20:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You swear to never\Nsteal artifacts
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.99,0:20:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Tenochtitlan\Nbasin again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.66,0:21:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.60,0:21:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll even write that\Nin my next book.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.73,0:21:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,YOUR next book?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean you're\Nactually A.K. Yearling!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.14,0:21:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell anypony!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.97,0:21:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives me an idea..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.41,0:21:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought your first\Nco-written novel
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.11,0:21:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,would bring out\Na ton of fans!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.75,0:21:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been upstaged\Nby a new author.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the noble Ahuizotl\Nbravely toiled day and night
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.89,0:21:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect the jungle's\Nprecious artifacts...
